-- tf.h3: `Step 5`: Personalise the business card

To personalise the card with your information:

- Open `index.ftd` document

- Click on the `edit` icon, to make the `index.ftd` document editable


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.edit-index-ftd.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

**`Note`**: Now replace the default data with your information

```
Example 1:

`John Doe` with `Ajit Garg`, `Chief Executive Officer` with `DevRel` etc.
```
```
Example 2:

You can remove the property entirely if you do not wish to provide that data.
```


-- tf.markdown:

- Click on the `Commit changes...` button

- If you wish you can put detail about the changes in popup, else click on 
`Commit changes` again.



-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.personalise-the-card.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

;; The `Actions` tab will have new workflow running, wait for it to complete.

- Once complete open the browser tab where your live site is running

- Refresh the browser


-- end: ftd.column







-- ftd.column:
width: fill-container
margin-vertical.px: 16

-- tf.h3: `Step 6`: Upload your logo

The output still has the default logo, so now we will personalise the logo.

It always good to put the image in one location. Here, we have `assets` 
folder where we can upload our logo file.

- Open the `assets` folder from `Code` tab


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.open-assets-folder.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

- Click on `Add file` and select `Upload files` option


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.upload-logo.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16



-- tf.markdown:

- Upload the file (in my case, file name is `fastn.svg`)

  `NOTE`: file name and extension can be anything for eg: *abc.png*, 
  *pqr.jpeg*, *xyz.svg*

- Once uploaded, commit your changes.


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.commit-uploaded-logo.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border

-- tf.markdown: 

Go back to the browser tab where your site is open and refresh the browser.

There you go you have your personalised business card ready.

-- end: ftd.column




